main event: Two airmen near Patrick AFB, Fla. reported sighting a red colored object larger than a star, moving in a zig-zag pulsating motion before disappearing into the overcast sky.
interesting points: The object was reported to have made no sound and its speed was undetermined.
The sighting lasted for approximately one minute, with no interception action taken.
Unsufficient data for evaluation led to the conclusion that it possibly was an airplane, but this was inconclusive.
The report indicates that there were no photographs or physical evidence of the sighting.
The sighting occurred around 2200 hours on 11 Feb 53, near the base theater at Patrick AFB.
sighted object: red colored object larger than a star, moving in a zig-zag pulsating motion
